article.description: Josh Fox scored 21 points with four rebounds as UC Davis beat Division II Fresno Pacific 76-46 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: UC Davis beats Div. II Fresno Pacific 76-46
article.linkText: UC Davis beats Div. II Fresno Pacific 76-46
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Josh Fox scored 21 points with four rebounds as UC Davis beat Division II Fresno Pacific 76-46 on Wednesday night. Fox did it with 7-of-10 shooting from the field for the Aggies (2-1). Siler Schneider scored 13 points and Lawrence White added 11 points with five rebounds. Schneider hit a 3-pointer midway through the first period to break a 12-12 tie and spark a 10-2 run that put the Aggies on top, 22-14 with 8:02 left in the half. They led 37-24 at the break. Schneider and Printup combined for a pair of 3s early in the second period to extend the Aggies' lead to 54-32 and from there, they never looked back. The Aggies hit 50 percent from the field overall, 76.9 percent from the line and had a 46-34 rebounding edge. Spencer Krannitz led the Sunbirds with 10 points, six rebounds and three steals.
